# Customer App 1.0 (Phase 28)

Read **[CUSTOMER_APP.md](../../CUSTOMER_APP.md)** before changes to customer routes, navigation, or centers.

## Layer ownership (mandatory before implementation)

| Surface | Owner |
|---------|-------|
| Customer App UI | **Customer App** (`app/app/`, `components/app/`) |
| Nav & route aliases | **Customer App** (`lib/app/nav-config.ts`, `route-aliases.ts`) |
| Business logic | **Aipify Core** (Supabase RPCs) — never in client panels |
| Platform Admin | **Platform** (`/platform/*`) — never mix into Customer App |

## Rules

1. Canonical routes are `/app/*` — `/dashboard/*` is legacy
2. Customer App must feel personal: "This is **my** Aipify"
3. Never expose other customers, platform billing controls, or global governance in Customer App
4. Health score, executive data, and feeds come from Core RPCs — panels are thin clients
5. All data tenant-scoped via `_presence_tenant_for_auth()` or equivalent
6. i18n required: `locales/{en,no,sv,da}/customerApp.json`
7. New customer features go under `app/app/` — not `app/platform/` or `app/dashboard/`
8. Command Center (`/app/command-center`) remains for desktop/advanced presence — Presence center is `/app/presence`

> Platform Admin is for Aipify Group AS. Customer App is for paying customers.
